description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Sexual Assault Referral Centre (SARC) provides services for everyone who have experienced rape and sexual assault. Our multidisciplinary team support’s people to access services including appropriate healthcare, forensic examination, specialist support services and therapeutic services. Our Services cover Devon, Torbay, Plymouth, Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The SARC has a specialist Children’s Trauma Therapy Service. We are looking for someone to join our team to provide highly specialist, evidence based therapies to children and young people within Devon and Torbay who have experienced rape or sexual assault. The post holder will also be required to support and line manage junior colleagues within the service alongside the Clinical Leads and Service Managers. This is an opportunity to join the SARC team in an exciting time of growth and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part time post of 15 Hours per Week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
